{
  "texts": [
    "While they are not without limitations, their potential in transforming educational assessment is considerable.",
    "Educators and institutions should harness these technologies judiciously, ensuring that the benefits of LLMs are fully realized while mitigating their inherent limitations.",
    "The development of automatic scoring algorithms began over a decade ago, primarily using token-based models in student responses, often referred to as the 'bag of words' approach 15, 27.",
    "These early models served as the foundation for current automatic scoring systems.",
    "The integration of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long short-term memory networks (LSTMs) has led to a substantial improvement in automatic scoring capabilities, significantly enhancing the accuracy of score predictions."
  ]
}